 parts of the monolingual dictionary entry, each time for a new set of lexemes. Frame semantics, conceptual metaphor theory, as well as cognitive conceptions of polysemy, are used to create a new example section for agentive nouns, a new defining structure for emotion terms and a new microstructural arrangement for particle entries. Dictionary analyses on all, as well as user studies on two of the features, complement these suggestions. The monograph thus presents a new approach to lexicography that incorporates into its description of lexical items how humans perceive and conceptualise language.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aCognitive grammar. 0aEnglish languagexLexicography. 4aCognitive Metaphor Theory. 4aCognitive Polysemy. 4aCognitive Semantics. 4aEinsprachiges Wörterbuch. 4aEnglish Monolingual Learner Dictionaries. 4aFrame Semantics. 4aFrame-Semantik. 4aKognitive Metapherntheorie. 4aKognitive Polysemie. 4aKognitive Semantik. 4aLernerwörterbuch. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2015z9783110438710oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831104242870 cprintz978311042744840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311042416440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110424164423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110424164.jpg  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-